insert into ARTICLE (id, language, content, external_url, title) values (1, 'pt', 'O Brasil &eacute; um pa&iacute;s formado por migrantes de v&aacute;rias regi&otilde;es, que em conjunto com os ind&iacute;genas nativos do territ&oacute;rio, contribu&iacute;ram para a constru&ccedil;&atilde;o de uma identidade brasileira multicultural. &#13;&#10; &#13;&#10;Conceitualmente, a migra&ccedil;&atilde;o internacional se refere ao movimento de pessoas que deixam os seus pa&iacute;ses de origem ou de resid&ecirc;ncia habitual para se fixarem, permanente ou temporariamente, em outro pa&iacute;s, implicando na travessia de fronteiras internacionais.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;A Organiza&ccedil;&atilde;o Internacional para as Migra&ccedil;&otilde;es (OIM), em seu Gloss&aacute;rio das Migra&ccedil;&otilde;es, recomenda que as pessoas vindas de outros pa&iacute;ses sejam identificadas como migrantes internacionais, ao inv&eacute;s de imigrantes ou estrangeiros, uma vez que esta mesma pessoa &eacute; emigrante no pa&iacute;s de origem, e imigrante no pa&iacute;s de destino, sendo a nomenclatura proposta mais eficiente para a identidade destas popula&ccedil;&otilde;es. O termo estrangeiro tamb&eacute;m &eacute; evitado, pois quer indicar que a pessoa &eacute; sempre uma estranha em rela&ccedil;&atilde;o ao pa&iacute;s em que se encontra.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Em uma vis&atilde;o mais abrangente, no grupo de migrantes internacionais pode-se incluir as pessoas em situa&ccedil;&atilde;o de ref&uacute;gio (refugiados), solicitantes de ref&uacute;gio ou ap&aacute;tridas, com o diferencial de terem sa&iacute;do de seus pa&iacute;ses contra sua vontade, conforme conceitua&ccedil;&atilde;o a seguir:&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; Refugiado, conforme artigo 1&ordm; da Lei Federal 9.474/1997, &eacute; pessoa que deixou seu pa&iacute;s de origem devido a fundados temores de persegui&ccedil;&atilde;o por motivos de ra&ccedil;a, religi&atilde;o, nacionalidade, grupo social ou opini&otilde;es pol&iacute;ticas, ou por grave e generalizada viola&ccedil;&atilde;o de direitos humanos, e que possuem essa condi&ccedil;&atilde;o reconhecida pelo pa&iacute;s em que se estabeleceram.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; Solicitante de ref&uacute;gio &eacute; o que ainda aguarda o reconhecimento como refugiado pelas autoridades competentes do pa&iacute;s em que se estabeleceu.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; Ap&aacute;trida, de acordo com a Lei Federal 4.246/2002, &eacute; termo que designa toda pessoa que n&atilde;o seja considerada nacional por nenhum pa&iacute;s, podendo tamb&eacute;m serem reconhecidas como refugiadas. A apatridia ocorre por v&aacute;rias raz&otilde;es, dentre elas conflitos territoriais entre pa&iacute;ses.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Ao chegarem ao Brasil, podem ter passado por uma longa e estressante jornada, permeada por situa&ccedil;&otilde;es adversas em seus pa&iacute;ses de origem ou no trajeto, como viol&ecirc;ncias, separa&ccedil;&otilde;es, lutos, persegui&ccedil;&otilde;es, guerras, dentre outras possibilidades. Assim, estas pessoas podem n&atilde;o possuir todos os documentos necess&aacute;rios para matr&iacute;cula, residirem em locais provis&oacute;rios, apresentarem dificuldades financeiras e outras situa&ccedil;&otilde;es que podem afetar os estudantes e seus familiares. &Eacute; imprescind&iacute;vel que os servidores da unidade escolar levem em considera&ccedil;&atilde;o todas essas possibilidades, a fim de proporcionar ao estudante migrante internacional um atendimento escolar digno e sem preconceitos.', 'https://deadamantina.educacao.sp.gov.br/estudantes-migrantes-internacionais/',  'Estudantes internacionais ');
insert into ARTICLE (id, language, content, external_url, title) values (1, 'en', 'Brazil is a country composed of migrants from various regions who, together with the native indigenous people of the territory, have contributed to the construction of a multicultural Brazilian identity. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Conceptually, international migration refers to the movement of people who leave their countries of origin or habitual residence to settle, either permanently or temporarily, in another country, involving the crossing of international borders. The International Organization for Migration (IOM), in its Migration Glossary, recommends that people coming from other countries be identified as international migrants, rather than immigrants or foreigners since the same person is an emigrant in the home country and an immigrant in the destination country. This proposed nomenclature is more efficient for the identity of these populations. The term foreigner is also avoided because it implies that the person is always a stranger in the country where they are. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;In a broader view, the group of international migrants can include people in refugee situations (refugees), asylum seekers, or stateless individuals, with the distinction of having left their countries against their will, as defined below: &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; A refugee, according to Article 1 of Federal Law 9,474/1997, is a person who has left their country of origin due to well-founded fears of persecution based on race, religion, nationality, social group, or political opinions, or due to serious and widespread human rights violations, and who has this condition recognized by the country in which they have settled.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; An asylum seeker is someone who is still awaiting recognition as a refugee by the competent authorities of the country in which they have settled.&#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;&bull; Stateless, according to Federal Law 4,246/2002, is a term that designates any person who is not considered a national by any country and can also be recognized as refugees. Statelessness occurs for various reasons, including territorial conflicts between countries. &#13;&#10;&#13;&#10;Upon arriving in Brazil, they may have gone through a long and stressful journey, marked by adverse situations in their home countries or along the way, such as violence, separations, mourning, persecution, wars, among other possibilities. Therefore, these individuals may not possess all the necessary documents for enrollment, may reside in temporary locations, may face financial difficulties, and other situations that can affect the students and their families. It is essential that school staff take all these possibilities into account in order to provide international migrant students with dignified and prejudice-free educational assistance.', 'https://deadamantina.educacao.sp.gov.br/estudantes-migrantes-internacionais/', 'International Students');
